<?xml version="1.0"?>
<block>
    <name>Symbol Generator</name>
    <key>gr_gs_SymbolGenerator</key>
    <category>[gr-gs]/Miscellaneous</category>
    <import>import gr_gs as gs</import>
    <make>gs.SymbolGenerator($weightings, $framingTag, $frameLength)</make>
    <callback>set_weightings($weightings)</callback>
    <callback>set_framingTag($framingTag)</callback>
    <callback>set_frameLength($frameLength)</callback>
    <param>
        <name>Symbol Weightings</name>
        <key>weightings</key>
        <value>[1]</value>
        <type>real_vector</type>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Framing Tag</name>
        <key>framingTag</key>
        <value>frame</value>
        <type>string</type>
        <hide>part</hide>
    </param>
    <param>
        <name>Frame Length</name>
        <key>frameLength</key>
        <value>0</value>
        <type>int</type>
        <hide>part</hide>
    </param>
    <source>
        <name>out</name>
        <type>@PYTHON_SYMBOL_TYPE@</type>
    </source>
    <doc>This block simply allows us to generate a random stream of uncorrelated symbols with discretely defined probability weightings. All we do is pass a vector of doubles where the double describes the weighting of the symbol as represented by the index of said vector. Thus a weighting vector of [1,1,1,2] would produce symbol values {0,1,2,3} with respective probabilities of {0.2, 0.2, 0.2, 0.4}. This block also has the ability to add framing tags at set intervals to aid in alignment.</doc>
</block>
